data.title: EastEnders' Jessie Wallace Over The Moon To Have Grandchild
data.meta_description: EastEnders star Jessie Wallace has become a granny for the first time after her 17-year-old daughter welcomed her first child.
data.text:
Soap star Jessie Wallace aka EastEnders' Kat Moon has surprised fans by announcing she's become a grandmother for the first time to a beautiful baby boy.

Taking to her Instagram, the 50-year-old shared a sweet black and white snap of the little one, who is called SJ.

She said: 'Welcome to the world, my grandson SJ. You are loved, cherished and adored.'

SJ's mum is Jessie's 17-year-old daughter Tallulah Lilac Morgan, who Jessie shares with her policeman ex Dave Morgan.

Lots of Jessie's co-stars and celebrity friends were quick to pass on congratulations to The Square's latest granny.

Fellow EastEnders star Lacey Turner said he is a 'Beautiful boy' while Suki Panesar actor Balvinder Sopal said: 'congratulations'.

Antony Costa from pop band Blue also joined in with his own message of congratulations.

Jessie joined EastEnders as Kat Slater back in 2000 and has been involved in numerous big storylines.

She was suspended from the soap in 2004 for alleged excessive partying, drinking and adverse publicity.

In 2020, she was suspended again for two months due to an alleged incident while filming.

Jessie has largely kept her daughter out of the spotlight but did reveal in 2019 that the teenager had been robbed by a gang in Muswell Hill, north London. At the time Tallulah was 14.

Congrats on the new addition, Jessie!
